			<p rend="letter-spacing: +2px">Statement</p>

			<p>Copied from the original statement signed by Mrs. <persName ref="#ehri_et_morgensternova_ruth">Ruth Morgensternová</persName>, residing
				in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3078610/brno.html">Brno</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3078610/brno.html">Na ponávce</placeName> 10</p>

			<p>former <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">prisoner</term> in the <placeName type="camp"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-42">Bergen-Belsen</placeName><term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentr. camp</term> and a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">labor camp</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/453733/republic-of-estonia.html">Estonia</placeName></p>

			<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-267" type="subject">Transport Be Theresienstadt</term> -
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/453733/republic-of-estonia.html">Estonia</placeName>.</p>

			<p><date when="1942-09-01">I. IX. 1942</date>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-267" type="subject">departure from Theresienstadt</term>,
				direction <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-1032">Riga</placeName>. The journey went well; the
				escort was decent. The <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522">train</term> stands
					in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-1032">Riga</placeName> for a day and then rides on to
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/453733/republic-of-estonia.html">Estonia</placeName>. After a five-day journey, the <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522">train</term> stops 25 km from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/588409/tallinn.html">Tallinn</placeName> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/589223/raasiku.html">Raasiku</placeName>. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term> and <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-356">SD</orgName>, with beautiful, blue buses, are waiting for us there.
				We stand in front of the <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522">train</term> and one <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SSman</term> selects the young people who will
				apparently be walking. The rest are told to put away their luggage and step onto the bus. We’ve heard no news of them since. We, the
				young ones (75 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> and about 150 <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term>), leave on trucks with all of the luggage
				from the <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521">transport</term> to the nearby <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/588409/tallinn.html">JAGALLA</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term>. It’s a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term> in the middle of a forest, with old,
				broken down <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837">buildings</term>, surrounded by a barbed
				wire fence. The <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-482">Lagerführer</term> is an <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/453733/republic-of-estonia.html">Estonian</placeName>
				<orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-356">SDman</orgName>; his adjutant a Baltic <term type="subject"
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German</term>. The guards are <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/453733/republic-of-estonia.html">Estonian</placeName>. Our valuables and extra <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836">clothes</term> are taken away on the first evening (body search). The
				next day, our <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836">clothes</term> are returned. Three
				days later, they lead us to large <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837">buildings</term>
				where we unpack and sort the items from our <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521"
					>transport</term>. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term>, whom we
				glimpse from far away, are sent to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">work</term> in
				the forest. Only the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">sick</term> return to us, and
				they are sent away, allegedly to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/588335/tartu.html">Dorpat</placeName>, where there is an
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-282" type="subject">infirmary</term>. Supposedly, the rest of the
					<term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521">transport</term> is there, but we never heard
				from any inhabitant of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/588335/tartu.html">Dorpat</placeName> that there were Jews there. <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">Women</term> are treated well; <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> fare far worse, especially when they <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">work</term> outside, where the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/453733/republic-of-estonia.html">Estonians</placeName> rob then and don’t give them anything to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">eat</term>. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term> is not bad; connection to the outside
				world is impossible. In <date when="1942-10">October</date>, another <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521">transport</term> arrives from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Germany</placeName> (<placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2925533/frankfurt-am-main.html">Frankfurt</placeName> and <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2950159/berlin.html">Berlin</placeName>). Once again, luggage and some of the people go to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/588409/tallinn.html">Jagälla</placeName>. In <date when="1942-12">December</date>, a large <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521">transport</term> of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> leaves for <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/588409/tallinn.html">Revala (Tallinn)</placeName> and supposedly to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/588335/tartu.html">Dorpat</placeName> (only the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-274" type="subject">older</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">sick</term>). The rest of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> (there are 45 of them and almost all are
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-279" type="subject">Czech</term>) move into very nice
					<term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837">buildings</term>. After their <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> in <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-48312" type="subject">Schleuse</term> is done, the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> go to the forest to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">chop</term> down trees and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">tear down</term> old buildings. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> is very hard. In <date when="1943-08"
					>August 1943</date>, the rest of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject"
					>women</term> leave for <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/588409/tallinn.html">Tallinn</placeName>; the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term> is liquidated. Before we leave, most of
				our things are taken away from us. In <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/588409/tallinn.html">Tallinn</placeName>, we <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">live</term> in the central <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-669" type="subject">prison</term>, where we meet up with the first <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521">transport</term>, and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> together doing cleaning <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> in the port under the supervision of the
					<orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-433">OT</orgName>. Here, we see the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> from our <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521">transport</term> who also return to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-669" type="subject">prison</term> after their <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> is done. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term> in <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-669" type="subject">prison</term> is terrible, but we can sometimes
				procure something for ourselves.</p>

			<p>In <date when="1943-12">December 1943</date>, all of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825"
					type="subject">women</term> leave <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/588409/tallinn.html">Tallinn</placeName> and go to
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/592258/ereda.html">EREDA</placeName> (about 30 km from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/590031/narva.html">Narva</placeName>). The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> remain in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/588409/tallinn.html">Tallinn</placeName>, and this is where we last hear from them in <date
					when="1944-03">March 1944</date>. <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/592258/ereda.html">Ereda</placeName> is a small <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term>. It already houses about 1,000 Jews
					from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/597427/republic-of-lithuania.html">Lithuania</placeName> (<placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Vilnius</placeName> and <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/598316/kaunas.html">Kovno</placeName>) and <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/458258/republic-of-latvia.html">Latvia</placeName>. They are <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-213" type="subject">lice-infested</term> and without their
				belongings. In the surrounding area, there are several other similar <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camps</term>. There are also several <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-279" type="subject">Czechs</term> there, arriving
					from <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-1032">Riga</placeName>. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term> has already taken leadership of it; guards
				are <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/453733/republic-of-estonia.html">Est.</placeName> and <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-433">O.T.</orgName> The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term> is bad, but we have the option to obtain
				things for ourselves, but only the fearless among us attempt this. We <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> in the forest and on the construction of a
				new <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term> a few km away. There is <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-493" type="subject">typhus</term>; there are <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">sick people</term>; <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-274" type="subject">the elderly</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> are constantly sent away (most likely
				to <placeName type="camp" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0">Auschwitz</placeName>). When the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004583">Russians</orgName> approach (in <date when="1944-07">July
					1944</date>), we depart for <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/588409/tallinn.html">Tallinn</placeName>, where a boat is
				supposed to be waiting for us. It’s not there, and so we go to a suburb of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/588409/tallinn.html">Tallinn</placeName> to a large meadow, where we stay for three weeks with no
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">shelter</term>. We <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556">dig trenches</term>. There is <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-569">famine</term> in the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term>. In <date when="1944-08">August</date>, we
				finally sail to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Germany</placeName>. We sail for
				five days without <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term>. We arrive in
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3099434/gdansk.html">Danzig</placeName> and sail down the <placeName
					ref="#ehri_et_vistula">Vistula</placeName> to <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-857"
					>Stutthof</placeName>. There, we are sent to the baths, our belongings are taken away, and we are given new <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836">clothes</term>. Our hair was already cut before we left <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/453733/republic-of-estonia.html">Estonia</placeName>. <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">Women</term> who are capable of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">working</term> leave for <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2911298/hamburg.html">Hamburg</placeName> after three weeks to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> in a munitions <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929">plant</term>. From there, we are evacuated in <date when="1945-04"
					>April 1945</date> to <placeName type="camp" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-42"
				>Bergen-Belsen</placeName>, <pb n="2" facs="EHRI-ET-JMP013_02.jpg"/> where we remain until <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">liberation</term>.</p>

